   "body" : "On a system with mining disabled and doing nothing but AddAddress calls according to the debug log, there are 80-120 IOPs per second (likely very small ops, because the total throughput is only ~1MB/s), which can bog a system down considerably.\r\n\r\nSome avenues of improvement might be:\r\n* Bulk puts\r\n* More selective storage of addresses\r\n* Disabling fsync for the address db",
